#: ../../theory/method.rst:2
msgid "DeePAW Method"
msgstr "DeePAW 方法"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:5
msgid "Method Overview"
msgstr "方法概述"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:7
msgid ""
"DeePAW (Deep Augmented Way) is a machine learning method for predicting "
"electron density functionals. Its name is inspired by the Projector "
"Augmented-Wave (PAW) method. DeePAW employs an E(3)-equivariant graph neural"
" network architecture based on the e3nn library, predicting electron "
"densities through end-to-end automated representation learning."
msgstr ""
"DeePAW（Deep Augmented Way）是一种用于预测电子密度泛函的机器学习方法，其命名灵感来源于投影缀加波（Projector "
"Augmented-Wave, PAW）方法。DeePAW 采用基于 e3nn 库的 E(3) "
"等变图神经网络架构，通过端到端自动表征学习实现电子密度预测。"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:10
msgid "Dual-Graph Message Passing Architecture"
msgstr "双图消息传递架构"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:12
msgid ""
"DeePAW adopts a Double Graph Message Passing Neural Network (Double Graph "
"MPNN) architecture comprising two collaborating MPNNs and an output head:"
msgstr "DeePAW 采用双图消息传递神经网络（Double Graph MPNN）架构，由两个协同工作的 MPNN 与一个输出头构成："

#: ../../theory/method.rst:14
msgid "**Atomic Representation**"
msgstr "**原子表征**"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:16
msgid ""
"The atomic representation module is responsible for learning atom-level "
"representations. Initial edge embeddings are constructed using Gaussian "
"basis functions (GBF):"
msgstr "原子表征模块负责学习原子层级表示。初始边嵌入由高斯基函数（Gaussian Basis Function, GBF）构建："

#: ../../theory/method.rst:18
msgid "e_{ij} = \\exp\\left(-\\frac{(d_{ij} - \\mu)^2}{2\\sigma^2}\\right)"
msgstr "e_{ij} = \\exp\\left(-\\frac{(d_{ij} - \\mu)^2}{2\\sigma^2}\\right)"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:22
msgid ""
"where :math:`d_{ij}` is the distance between nodes i and j, and :math:`\\mu`"
" is uniformly distributed between 0 and 6 |angstrom|."
msgstr ""
"其中 :math:`d_{ij}` 为节点 i 与 j 之间的距离，:math:`\\mu` 在 0 至 6 |angstrom| 之间均匀分布。"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:24
msgid ""
"The message function constructs equivariant messages using Clebsch-Gordan "
"coefficients and spherical harmonics; each atom aggregates messages from all"
" neighbors before updating its node embedding. A dynamic rotation angle "
"mechanism is introduced during node embedding updates, dynamically adjusting"
" the directional information of equivariant features through the gating "
"mechanism of e3nn."
msgstr ""
"消息函数利用 Clebsch-Gordan "
"系数与球谐函数构造等变消息；每个原子在更新节点嵌入前会聚合其所有邻居的消息。在节点嵌入更新过程中，引入动态旋转角机制，通过 e3nn "
"的门控机制动态调节等变特征的方向信息。"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:28
msgid "**Electronic Potential**"
msgstr "**电子势**"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:30
msgid ""
"The electronic potential module operates at the level of grid points. Node "
"embeddings from the atomic representation are fed into the electronic "
"potential module, where grid points update their own embeddings by "
"aggregating information from neighboring atomic nuclei. Shared weight "
"vectors and interaction weight vectors are used during the embedding update "
"to control the relative contributions of a node's own features and the "
"incoming neighbor messages."
msgstr ""
"电子势模块在网格点层级运行。来自原子表征模块的节点嵌入被输入电子势模块，网格点通过聚合邻近原子核信息更新其自身嵌入。在嵌入更新过程中引入共享权重向量与交互权重向量，用以控制节点自身特征与邻居消息输入的相对贡献。"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:32
msgid "**Output Heads**"
msgstr "**输出头**"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:34
msgid "The output head comprises three modules:"
msgstr "输出头由三个模块组成："

#: ../../theory/method.rst:36
msgid ""
"**GAT head**: Based on a Graph Attention Network (GAT), it extracts atom-"
"level output quantities from the node embeddings of all layers of the atomic"
" representation."
msgstr ""
"**GAT head**：基于图注意力网络（Graph Attention Network, GAT），从原子表征各层的节点嵌入中提取原子层级输出量。"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:37
msgid ""
"**MLP head**: Generates a smoothly varying electron density profile from the"
" node embeddings of all layers of the electronic potential module."
msgstr "**MLP head**：由电子势模块各层节点嵌入生成平滑变化的电子密度分布。"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:38
msgid ""
"**KAN head**: Based on a Kolmogorov-Arnold Network (KAN), it computes the "
"residual electron density from the node embeddings of the final layer of the"
" electronic potential module."
msgstr "**KAN head**：基于 Kolmogorov-Arnold Network（KAN），由电子势模块末层节点嵌入计算电子密度残差。"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:41
msgid "Charge Density Grid Construction"
msgstr "电荷密度网格构建"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:43
msgid ""
"DeePAW constructs the electron density grid following VASP's coarse-fine "
"grid scheme. The grid density is determined according to the Nyquist-Shannon"
" sampling theorem to ensure adequate sampling of the electron density field."
msgstr ""
"DeePAW 依据 VASP 的粗细网格方案构建电子密度网格。网格密度根据 Nyquist-Shannon 采样定理确定，以保证对电子密度场的充分采样。"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:45
msgid ""
"Users must specify the grid dimensions (nx, ny, nz) when using the platform."
" These three parameters determine:"
msgstr "用户在使用平台时必须指定网格维度（nx、ny、nz）。这三个参数决定："

#: ../../theory/method.rst:47
msgid ""
"The sampling resolution of the charge density in three-dimensional space."
msgstr "三维空间中电荷密度的采样分辨率。"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:48
msgid "The total number of probe points to be predicted (nx * ny * nz)."
msgstr "待预测探针点总数（nx * ny * nz）。"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:49
msgid "The grid dimensions of the output CHGCAR file."
msgstr "输出 CHGCAR 文件的网格维度。"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:51
msgid ""
"The Cartesian coordinates of grid points are obtained by transforming "
"fractional coordinates with the unit cell matrix:"
msgstr "网格点的笛卡尔坐标由分数坐标经晶胞矩阵变换得到："

#: ../../theory/method.rst:53
msgid ""
"\\mathbf{r}_{ijk} = \\frac{i}{n_x} \\mathbf{a} + \\frac{j}{n_y} \\mathbf{b} "
"+ \\frac{k}{n_z} \\mathbf{c}"
msgstr ""
"\\mathbf{r}_{ijk} = \\frac{i}{n_x} \\mathbf{a} + \\frac{j}{n_y} \\mathbf{b} "
"+ \\frac{k}{n_z} \\mathbf{c}"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:57
msgid ""
"where :math:`\\mathbf{a}, \\mathbf{b}, \\mathbf{c}` are the unit cell basis "
"vectors."
msgstr ""
"其中 :math:`\\mathbf{a}, \\mathbf{b}, \\mathbf{c}` 为晶胞基矢。"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:60
msgid "Training Strategy"
msgstr "训练策略"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:62
msgid "DeePAW training proceeds in two stages using the L1 loss function:"
msgstr "DeePAW 采用 L1 损失函数并分两个阶段进行训练："

#: ../../theory/method.rst:64
msgid ""
"**Stage 1**: The MLP head and GAT head are jointly trained, optimizing for "
"electron density prediction."
msgstr "**阶段 1**：联合训练 MLP head 与 GAT head，优化电子密度预测。"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:65
msgid ""
"**Stage 2**: The MLP head is trained with a very small learning rate while "
"the KAN head uses a larger learning rate, implementing an adaptive PAW "
"scheme that captures the fine structure of the residual electron density."
msgstr ""
"**阶段 2**：MLP head 采用极小学习率训练，同时 KAN head 采用较大学习率训练，以实现自适应 PAW "
"方案并捕捉残余电子密度的精细结构。"

#: ../../theory/method.rst:67
msgid ""
"Training data are sourced from the Materials Project (MP) database. Electron"
" density labels are computed from KSDFT orbital wavefunctions using VASP."
msgstr "训练数据来源于 Materials Project（MP）数据库。电子密度标签由 VASP 基于 KSDFT 轨道波函数计算获得。"
